In general, objects in the audit events don't have variables as keys.
I'm pointing this out because it is different from the responses of the GET APIs that can return multiple values.
But our "set" APIs, which are the ones that this PR is concerned with, only act on single objects, and
I think that having a "name": "dummy", ... field is more straightforward and easier to parse than keying with the value of the name (or equivalent) attribute, eg "enabled": {"user": {"name": "test"}} vs "enabled": {"user": "test"}.
Let me know if we need to discuss this further.

