replies.bodyText:
I would support cleaning up the request object so that it didn't support different styles of "empty" strings - it may be as simple as changing the setters to have
if( Strings.hasText(arg) ) {
   this.field = arg;
} else 
   this.field = null;
}

But, I'm not sure there's a good reason to squeeze that into this PR.
I think the current logging is the preferred behaviour - or at least we should always print them as a pair, I don't have a string view whether we should output the match-all fields as *, _all or null.
The user and realm are a pair. They work as a pair, and they should be printed as a pair.

